cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS, cs.MM

This paper deals with a deep learning approach for anatomical landmarking using cone-beam computed tomography (CBCT) scans. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a new deep network architecture called relational reasoning network (RRN), which learns the local and global relations of the landmarks. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of dense-block units, which are commonly used in medical imaging, indicating that it could belong to cs.MS (Medical Imaging) as well. Finally, the paper deals with the craniomaxillofacial (CMF) bones, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
